---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Training — grimbergIT">
  <article class="surface">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workshops</p>
    <h1>Training</h1>
    <p>
      Hands-on workshops, in-house or remote. I teach the way I learned: by breaking things on
      purpose and putting them back together.
    </p>

    <h2>Formats</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>One-day intensives (small groups, dense hands-on).</li>
      <li>Multi-week cohorts with weekly sessions and homework repos.</li>
      <li>Custom curriculum for internal enablement teams.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Topics I teach often</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Kubernetes from first principles (no YAML worship).</li>
      <li>Observability that pays for itself.</li>
      <li>Go for people who already know another language.</li>
      <li>Writing better tests (TDD without the dogma).</li>
    </ul>

    <p><a href="/contact">Book a session →</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
